          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          Israel‚Äôs offensive plans
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/israel-gaza-offensive-escalation-occupation-plan.png" alt="Israel has approved a plan to escalate the offensive in Gaza, including the occupation of the Gaza Strip and continued control over captured areas" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Israel has approved a plan to escalate the offensive in Gaza, including the occupation of the Gaza Strip and continued control over captured areas. Credits: AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           PM Benjamin Netanyahu said the security cabinet had decided on a "<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-forceful-operation" target="_blank">forceful operation</a>" to destroy Hamas. The aim is to "conquer" the territory and sustain a presence. Israeli forces will advance deeper into Gaza, pushing civilians south while strengthening control over key areas. The plan aims to limit UN-led aid and replace it with Israeli-run hubs.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Netanyahu continues to promote Donald Trump‚Äôs proposal of the ethnic cleansing of Gaza. Humanitarian organizations have condemned the restrictions on aid distribution hubs, and Hamas has described the move as ‚Äúpolitical blackmail.‚Äù The Israeli government faces pressure from far-right coalition partners to reoccupy Gaza, but a significant faction of Israeli society is jaded by the war and actively protesting this. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Meanwhile, Hamas also has internal friction. They recently set a curfew and are <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-executing-people" target="_blank">executing people</a> for allegedly looting. Many Gazans are in a dire situation and find Hamas counterproductive in getting Israel to halt strikes. Trump‚Äôs visit to the Middle East could impact ceasefire talks and humanitarian aid.
         </p>
        
        </mj-text>
