      <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">US bases in Europe
       </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: Trump‚Äôs second term has sparked speculation about the US withdrawing from its European military bases.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           What is the future of transatlanticism? Trump's second term brought <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-analysis-h1-5-renewed-speculation" target="_blank">renewed speculation</a> about a potential US troop withdrawal from Germany. Experts and local officials say such a move is unlikely in the near future. Around 37,000 American troops remain stationed in Germany, primarily at Ramstein Air Base and other installations in Rhineland-Palatinate.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          In a recent interview with the Center for European Policy Analysis, retired General Wesley  Clark <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-analysis-h1-6-stressed-the-importance" target="_blank">stressed the importance</a> of the US military presence in Europe. He believes it is crucial for global security and deterrence. He warns that Eastern Europe is a geopolitical tinderbox under Russian pressure.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Any US withdrawal could signal weakness to both Moscow and Beijing. He pointed out that bases like Ramstein, Rota, and Lakenheath help project US power and support Ukraine‚Äôs defense. Forward deployments in NATO‚Äôs eastern flank are not just symbolic. They provide training, deterrence, and quick response capabilities.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Clark is critical of the US‚Äôs strategic shift toward Asia and says that abandoning Europe could destabilize a key part of the international structure. He warns against surrendering military readiness in Europe, and the US's credibility depends on staying engaged.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
