      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá∫üá¶ Ukraine - Zelenskyy warns foreign delegations.</strong> Zelenskyy warned that Ukraine cannot assure the safety of foreign delegations visiting Moscow for the May 9 Victory Day Parade. He expressed concerns that Russia could stage provocations, such as bombings, and blame Ukraine. Russian officials criticized his statement (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-worldwide-h1-7-strong-warning" target="_blank">strong warning</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá¨üá¶ Gabon - President sworn in.</strong> Brice Oligui Nguema was sworn in as president, pledging democratic renewal after leading a 2023 coup. He vowed to unite the nation, reduce youth unemployment, and diversify the oil-dependent economy. His inauguration follows a landslide election victory and marks a return to the constitutional ways (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-worldwide-h2-8-revival-of-democracy" target="_blank">revival of democracy</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá∑üáº Rwanda - Talks with the US.</strong> Rwanda is discussing accepting deported migrants from the US. The discussions follow US efforts to establish international partnerships for deporting foreign nationals amid crackdowns on visa holders and criminal suspects. Rwanda has previously offered to house deported criminals and failed asylum seekers for Western nations (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-worldwide-h3-9-early-discussions" target="_blank">early discussions</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üá∑üá¥ Romania - PM resigns and fall of coalition.</strong> Romanian PM Marcel Ciolacu resigned after his coalition's candidate lost in the presidential election's first round. Right-wing Nationalist George Simion led with 40.5% and will face pro-EU mayor Nicu»ôor Dan in the May 18 runoff. Ciolacu urged his party to exit the ruling coalition (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-worldwide-h4-10-political-turmoil" target="_blank">political turmoil</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>üáÆüá∑ Iran - Abbas Araghchi visits Pakistan.</strong> 
           Iranian FM Abbas Araghchi arrived in Islamabad for a one-day visit to discuss rising tensions between Pakistan and India following an attack in disputed Kashmir. While specific discussions were not confirmed, the Iranian ambassador stated the visit would address ways to de-escalate tensions. Araghchi is also expected to visit India later this week (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-worldwide-h5-11-diplomatic-talks" target="_blank">diplomatic talks</a>). 
          </p>
          
        </mj-text>
